Patch summary:
Bound host-visible Vulkan memory retained by GPU drivers which fail to release
imported dma-bufs. Keep a renderer-wide exact-size pool of udmabuf objects and
reuse their backing memfds across VkEmulation and guest process lifetimes
instead of creating a new dma-buf for every allocation cycle.

Carry a shared lease through both owners of the backing allocation: the host
VkDeviceMemory and the virtio-gpu blob resource exported to the VMM. An entry
does not become reusable until both owners are gone, with a short quarantine to
avoid racing the VMM's final descriptor close.

After the renderer cleanup worker has waited for the guest process render
threads, destroyed the Vulkan/GL resources, and released ProcessResources,
trim glibc arenas on this udmabuf-specific path. Otherwise hundreds of MiB of
already-free per-render-thread allocations remain resident after every game
launch even though the graphics objects are gone.

